                                 <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>THREE EXTRA TRAIN TOURS to CAPE TOWN in DECEMBER 2010</strong></font></td>
                               </tr>
                             </tbody>
                           </table>
                           <div style="float: left; padding: 5px;"><img src="http://www.jbtours.co.za/images/newsletter/aug-2010/cape-town.JPG" nosend="1" alt="Cape Town" /></div>
                           <p>The popularity of our <strong>Jo’burg to Cape Town</strong> train tours during December has again exceeded all expectations. ALL the tours are fully booked and the enquiries and bookings keep on coming in. In stead of overcrowding the current tours, we have rather <strong>organised three extra train tours</strong> during the peak period – to be hosted at the <strong>same tour price</strong>. The new dates are: 15 – 21 Dec, 22 – 28 Dec &amp; 29 Dec – 4 Jan ’11. <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-cape-town-holiday.php">More info</a></p>
                           <p>These tours are very popular with families and people who can only take leave in December every year. </p>
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                             <tbody>
                               <tr>
                                 <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>NEW Jo’burg to Port Elizabeth TRAIN TOUR</strong></font></td>
                               </tr>
                             </tbody>
                           </table>
                           <p>The   news that the Trans Natal Tourist Class train running between Jo&rsquo;burg and Durban   has been permanently stopped by Shosholoza Meyl, affected many of our scheduled   tours for the rest of the year and of course in future. It means that our   Durban long   weekend tours had to be abandoned, whilst the &ldquo;7 Provinces &amp; 3 Trains&rdquo; tour   now becomes a &ldquo;7 Provinces, 2 Trains and one Bus&rdquo;   tour.</p>
                           <p>However, the Durban weekend train tour has been replaced by a similar   tour to Port Elizabeth &ndash; the Friendly City. At the same tour price. The dates   for 2010 are almost the same, whilst the price remains unchanged as   well.</p>
                           <p>The   train departs on a Friday morning from Jo&rsquo;burg, arrives at 08:00 in PE, the   whole day, night and next morning is spent in PE and at 13:00 it departs again   back to Jo&rsquo;burg to arrive at 09:40 Monday morning. Go and re-discover PE and all   its sight seeing spots and beaches. <a href="http://jbtours.co.za/2010-port-elizabeth-holiday.php">More Info</a></p>
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                             <tbody>
                               <tr>
                                 <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>HUISGENOOT SKOUSPEL (by Sun City)  – Vlugte vanuit Kaapstad, George, PE &amp; Durban</strong></font></td>
                               </tr>
                             </tbody>
                           </table>
                           <p>Die   kunstenaars wat aan die 2010 Huisgenoot Skouspel in Oktober by Sun City gaan deelneem, is onlangs bekend gemaak. Dit lyk   soos die &lsquo;Wie&rsquo;s wie&rsquo; van top Afrikaanse kunstenaars in Suid-Afrika. Om hulle saam in een aand op &lsquo;n verhoog te sien (selfs   almal tergelykertyd op die verhoog op &lsquo;n stadium) is &lsquo;n belewenis. Die groot   simfonie orkes wat saam optree verseker ho&euml; musiek-kwaliteit. Wees daar. Die   kunstenaars is: </p>
                           <p>Kurt Darren, Nicholis Louw, Theuns   Jordaan, Juanita du Plessis, Nianell, Mara Louw, Andriette Norman, Bok van   Blerk, SA Jeugkoor, George Longane, Karin Ferreira, Coenie de Villiers, Rina   Hugo, Emo Adams, Carike Keuzenkamp, Brandon October, Sonja Herholdt, Wicus van   der Merwe, Jennifer Jones, Cheree, Jay van Eden, Flip-a-coin, Heinz Winckler,   Snotkop, Gerhard Steyn, Romanz, Ray Dylan, Bobby van Jaarsveld asook Rudi &amp;   Corlea. </p>
                           <p>Die jaarlikse <strong>Huisgenoot Skouspel</strong> wat in <strong>Oktober</strong> by <strong>Sun City </strong>in Noordwes aangebied word, beloof weer ‘n groot Skouspel te wees. Dit is die 11de jaar wat dit aangebied word en elke jaar is al 7 die vertonings, met bykans 5000 mense per vertoning, uitverkoop. JB Train Tours reël reeds die afgelope klompie jare bustoere vanuit Johannesburg, Pretoria, asook die Oos en Wes Rand na hierdie feesgeleentheid waar sowat 40 bekende Afrikaanse musikante optree. <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-huisgenoot-skouspel.php">Meer inligting</a> Vanjaar is   daar ook &lsquo;n <strong>bustoer</strong> vanaf Nelspruit   gere&euml;l, wat een nag se verblyf insluit. <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-huisgenoot-skouspel-nelspruit.php">Meer   inligting</a>. Ons het ook 'n bustoer vanuit VanderBijlpark en Potchefstroom vir Sondag 3 Oktober 2010 gere&euml;l <a href="../2010-huisgenoot-skouspel-potch.php">Meer inligting</a></p>
                           <p>Sedert 2008 bied ons   ewe gewilde 3-dag naweek <strong>vliegpakkette</strong> vanaf Kaapstad,   George, Port Elizabeth en Durban na die Skouspel toe   aan. <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-huisgenoot-skouspel-kaapstad.php">Meer   inligting</a>. Hierdie toerpakket sluit ook verblyf, busvervoer,   sekere etes en natuurlik die Huisgenoot Skouspel kaartjie   in.</p>
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                             <tbody>
                               <tr>
                                 <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>2010 VODACOM DURBAN JULY - Travel in style by Premier Classe train</strong></font></td>
                               </tr>
                             </tbody>
                           </table>
                           <div style="float: left; padding: 5px;"><img src="http://jbtours.co.za/images/newsletter/sept-2010/durban-july.JPG" nosend="1" alt="Durban July" /></div>
                           <p>The Vodacom July Handicap in Durban is one of   the&nbsp;<strong>most prestigious horse   races</strong>&nbsp;in the country. It is an occasion where full bred horses, the   rich and famous, the beautiful and the mod, as well as the &lsquo;man on the street&rsquo;   meet to enjoy a day of fun, horse racing, good food and wine, new designer   dresses and betting. If you have always dreamed of attending   it and never got to it, book a place on the&nbsp;<strong>specially arranged train</strong>&nbsp;tour from Jo&rsquo;burg   to Durban over   the weekend of 30th July to 2nd August 2010 on the upmarket&nbsp;<span style="color:#93C">Premier Classe </span>train.</p>
                           <p><strong>The   above tour was our first train tour to the &lsquo;July&rsquo; and it was fully booked &ndash; book   now for next year! </strong><a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/upmarket/2011-durban-july-stylish-weekend.php">More   info</a></p>
                           <p>It was very   popular with groups and as incentives.</p>
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                             <tbody>
                               <tr>
                                 <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>CELEBRATE NEW YEAR’S EVE on the Train - NEW TOUR!</strong></font></td>
                               </tr>
                             </tbody>
                           </table>
                           <div style="float: left; padding:5px;"><img src="http://jbtours.co.za/images/newsletter/sept-2010/champaine-classes.JPG" style="border:double thick #000;" nosend="1" alt="New Year's eve" /></div>
                           <p>Have you ever enjoyed a New Years Eve on a train? JB   Train Tours have organised a Durban Stylish 2011 <em>New Years Eve</em> weekend from JHB for only R3   999pp sharing. Dates: 31 Dec to 3 Jan 2011 (Fri &ndash; Mon) </p>
                           <p>Included in the package is your return overnight trip on   the upmarket <strong>Premier Classe </strong>train   (incl. 5-course meals &amp; bedding on train), transfers between DBN Train   Station in hotel, 1 night B&amp;B in a 4-star Hotel on the beach   front. </p>
                           <p><strong><a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/upmarket/2011-durban-stylish-weekend.php">Book   now</a></strong><strong> &ndash; limited   spaces available.</strong></p>
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                             <tbody>
                               <tr>
                                 <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>CORPORATE STYLISH WEEKEND GET-AWAYS</strong></font></td>
                               </tr>
                             </tbody>
                           </table>
                           <p>It is that time of the year again when <strong>Marketing &amp; Event Managers</strong> start   searching for ideas for their company&rsquo;s <strong>Year   End function</strong> and/or <strong>Incentive   get-aways</strong>. </p>
                           <p>We know people expect from you to offer something   different &ndash; something that would <strong>WOW</strong> them! </p>
                           <p>JB Train Tours offers various customized stylish weekend   get aways to places like Durban, Cape Town, Oudtshoorn &amp;   PE. Everything will be organized on your behalf: an upmarket train trip on the <strong><span style="color:#990099;">Premier   Classe</span></strong> train, 5-course meals on the train, excursions off the   train, accommodation on &amp; off the train, welcome drinks, pillow gifts,   shuttle and many more services. </p>
                           <p>Don&rsquo;t be disappointed by booking too late. Enquiry today   with <U><a href="mailto:jolene@jbtours.co.za">Jolene</a></U> about exciting train tour options.</p>
                           <div style="clear:both;"></div>
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                             <tbody>
                               <tr>
                                 <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>TEMPORARY SUSPENSION of LONG DISTANCE TRAINS in SOUTH AFRICA</strong></font></td>
                               </tr>
                             </tbody>
                           </table>
                           <p>It is   common knowledge that all longs distance trains in South Africa   were suspended by Shosholoza Meyl on Wednesday the 11th August 2010 &ndash;   without any pre-warning &ndash; for 2 weeks. <strong>Shosholoza   Meyl</strong> forms part of &lsquo;<strong>Prasa</strong>&rsquo; (Passenger Rail Agency   of South Africa) which is a parastatal of the Government. The suspension derived   from a dispute between Prasa and   Transnet about the maintenance of locomotives (hauling the   trains).</p>
                           <p>The   unfortunate result was that only a limited number of workable/operational   locomotives were available, leading to trains being cancelled on short notice,   leading to <strong>paid-up PRASA passengers being stranded at   stations</strong>. In some cases alternative bus transport was made   available to passengers. All these cancellations <strong>affected JB   Train Tours&rsquo;   tours</strong> during August 2010 negatively. <strong>At least   13</strong> of our tours had to be re-scheduled, re-organised   and re-vamped &ndash; all on <strong>VERY</strong> short notice. Only one   tour could not be re-organised (The rugby train tour from JHB to CPT). The time   limited and unavailability of resources prevented us from doing   so.</p>
                           <p>Obviously the re-arranged tours did   not suit everyone&rsquo;s individual needs, but we have had <strong>two   choices</strong> about these tours: <strong>Firstly:</strong> We could have   cancelled the tours (<em>the easy way   out</em>), informed the passengers accordingly, wait for all   the complaints, moans and groans, respond to it and do all the refunds <strong>OR Secondly:</strong> We could try <strong>to salvage   all the tours</strong> to the best of our ability with the resources   available &amp; service providers willing to assist. We have decided on the   latter. <strong>AND   WE ARE VERY PROUD ON WHAT WE&rsquo;VE ACHIEVED.</strong></p>
                           <p>It   took lots of extra work (including after hours), lateral thinking, fruitful   negotiations with service providers (airlines, bus companies, hotels, etc.) to   make it happen. One should keep in mind that re-organising 45 passengers per tour to   change travel arrangements form a train to a flight or bus does not happen   quickly. The JB Train Tours team worked non-stop to make this   happen. </p>
                           <p>Our <strong>appreciation</strong> and<strong> thanks</strong> to everyone who has sent us e-mails &amp; faxes, as   well as telephone calls, with kind words of appreciation for making the tours   continue. At this very moment (end of August 2010) trains are <strong>NOT</strong> back to normal, except   for the <strong><span style="color:#990099;">Premier   Classe</span></strong> on certain routes, despite press releases by   Shosholoza Meyl to that extend as well as articles in   newspapers.</p>
                           <p>JB   Train Tours are still very committed to <strong>Rail   Tourism</strong> in South Africa and will continue to be   involved and make it happen as long as it is practical   possible.</p>
